      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "aliphatic-amines",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>Only $1^{\\circ}$ or primary amines gives positive carbylamines test.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m9p17r5z/e5509ec3-0d00-4635-b5e4-6ab99f9575ba/b305b570-1d8f-11f0-8528-f36c523d5a7b/file-jaoe38c1m9p17r60.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m9p17r5z/e5509ec3-0d00-4635-b5e4-6ab99f9575ba/b305b570-1d8f-11f0-8528-f36c523d5a7b/file-jaoe38c1m9p17r60.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 7th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 31 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Option (A) and (C) are primary amine and given $\\oplus \\mathrm{ve}$ carbyl amine test</p>",
